1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:04,340
Sometimes an error in one part of your code affects other parts,

2

00:00:04,340  -->  00:00:06,220
much like a malfunctioning ride at

3

00:00:06,220  -->  00:00:09,340
the theme park impacting other areas of the park as well.

4

00:00:09,340  -->  00:00:11,660
Components can often be interconnected,

5

00:00:11,660  -->  00:00:16,200
and the effect from one is felt in one or more places elsewhere.

6

00:00:16,200  -->  00:00:19,880
Python allows exceptions to be passed or propagated to

7

00:00:19,880  -->  00:00:24,160
higher levels in the code where they can be handled more broadly.

8

00:00:24,160  -->  00:00:28,320
This way, an error in a specific function can bubble up and be

9

00:00:28,320  -->  00:00:32,780
managed by a function at a higher level. That's a lot.

10

00:00:32,780  -->  00:00:36,955
What exactly does that mean when we're writing Python code?

11

00:00:36,955  -->  00:00:39,530
Imagine we have a ticket purchasing function

12

00:00:39,530  -->  00:00:42,730
that relies on another function to verify funds.

13

00:00:42,730  -->  00:00:46,510
If an exception occurs in the funds checking function,

14

00:00:46,510  -->  00:00:49,950
it can propagate up to the ticket purchasing function.

15

00:00:49,950  -->  00:00:53,210
This can be a helpful way to make interrelated functions,

16

00:00:53,210  -->  00:00:56,450
while also making sure that if any errors occur,

17

00:00:56,450  -->  00:00:58,495
they can still be found.

18

00:00:58,495  -->  00:01:02,260
Also, since we are decompartmentalizing our code,

19

00:01:02,260  -->  00:01:06,300
instead of making a monolith function with everything in it,

20

00:01:06,300  -->  00:01:09,000
we can make individual functions and

21

00:01:09,000  -->  00:01:12,500
handle them separately rather than all in the same place.

22

00:01:12,500  -->  00:01:18,105
If we run this function such as passing a -10 into purchase ticket -10,

23

00:01:18,105  -->  00:01:20,640
this will return ticket purchase failed.

24

00:01:20,640  -->  00:01:22,260
Funds cannot be negative.

25

00:01:22,260  -->  00:01:24,360
The value error raised in

26

00:01:24,360  -->  00:01:29,600
the check funds function propagates up to purchase ticket where we handle it.

27

00:01:29,600  -->  00:01:33,480
This flow ensures that the ticket purchasing process is robust,

28

00:01:33,480  -->  00:01:38,080
catching any underlying issues and handling them appropriately.
